10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Tallyfy is best suited for small businesses, process documentation, client workflows, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Zoho Flow, meanwhile, shines for Zoho users, small businesses, budget conscious teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Tallyfy describes itself as \"Process and workflow management for documenting and tracking business procedures.\" Zoho Flow, established in 1996, positions itself as \"Integration platform connecting Zoho and third-party apps with automated workflows.\" With 19 years between them, Zoho Flow brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Tallyfy offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Zoho Flow** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 7), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Tallyfy is a poor choice — far from it. Tallyfy excels in its own right, particularly for small businesses and process documentation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent value within zoho ecosystem, go with Zoho Flow. If simple process documentation matters more to you, Tallyfy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
